 Ashford Chairman & CEO, Monty J. Bennett, To Present At 2016 Milken Institute Global Conference 
         










    










 













 











 



















Ashford Chairman & CEO, Monty J. Bennett, To Present At 2016 Milken Institute Global Conference
        																																						
              











 News provided by
Ashford Inc.  
Apr 28, 2016, 13:15 ET









 Share this article




























































DALLAS, April 28, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- Ashford Inc., (NYSE MKT: AINC) ("Ashford" or the "Company"), a leading provider of global asset management, investment management and related services to the real estate and hospitality sectors, today announced that Monty J. Bennett, Founder, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Ashford Group of Companies, will be a panelist at the 2016 Milken Institute Global Conference taking place May 1, 2016 – May 4, 2016 in Los Angeles, CA.








Mr. Bennett's panel, titled "U.S. Overview: Will Recovery Prevail?" will examine whether the U.S. economic rebound remains on solid footing, given an array of geopolitical risks and domestic challenges. He will be joined by several other panelists, including Fred Hochberg, Chairman and President, Export-Import Bank of the United States; Judith McKenna, Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer, Walmart U.S.; and Bluford Putnam, Chief Economist and Managing Director, Strategic Intelligence and Analytics, CME Group.
The panel will be available for live-streaming and video replay on the Milken Institute Global Conference website.
Ashford provides global asset management, investment management and related services to the real estate and hospitality sectors.
Follow Chairman and CEO Monty Bennett on Twitter at www.twitter.com/MBennettAshford or @MBennettAshford.  
To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit:http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/ashford-chairman--ceo-monty-j-bennett-to-present-at-2016-milken-institute-global-conference-300259503.html
SOURCE  Ashford Inc.



 












